tr: filled or smeared with offensive matter
example: a nasty pigsty of a room

tr: exasperatingly difficult to handle or circumvent
example: a good man to have on your side in a tight situation
Will he say nasty things at my funeral?"- Ezra Poun

value.def: Something that is nasty is very unpleasant to see, experience, or feel.

example.tran: 这场离婚可能会撕破脸。

value.tran: 令人不快的;令人厌恶的;恶劣的

value.def: If you describe a person or their behaviour as nasty, you mean that they behave in an unkind and unpleasant way.

example.ex: What nasty little snobs you all are...
example.tran: 你们全都是些可恶的势利小人。

example.ex: Mummy is so nasty to me when Daddy isn't here.
example.tran: 爸爸不在这儿时，妈妈对我很凶。

example.ex: She took the money and eyed me nastily...
example.tran: 她拿了钱，恶狠狠地打量着我。

example.ex: As the years went by his nastiness began to annoy his readers.
example.tran: 年深日久，他恶毒的文字开始让读者生厌。

value.def: If you describe something as nasty, you mean it is unattractive, undesirable, or in bad taste.

example.tran: 埃米莉在巴勒姆的脏乱小屋

example.ex: That damned Farrel made some nasty jokes here about Mr. Lane.
example.tran: 那个该死的法雷尔开了些关于莱恩先生的下流玩笑。

value.tran: 邋遢的;低劣的;下流的;污秽的

value.def: A nasty problem or situation is very worrying and difficult to deal with.

example.ex: A spokesman said this firm action had defused a very nasty situation.
example.tran: 一位发言人称这一坚决的行动缓和了极为棘手的局面。

value.def: If you describe an injury or a disease as nasty, you mean that it is serious or looks unpleasant.

example.ex: My little granddaughter caught her heel in the spokes of her bicycle — it was a very nasty wound...
example.tran: 我小孙女的脚跟夹到自行车的轮辐里了，伤得很严重。

example.ex: Lili had a nasty chest infection.

value.def: Nasties are unpleasant or harmful people or things.

example.tran: 充斥着恶棍的邪恶组织

example.ex: Decaffeinated coffee still contains some stimulants and other nasties linked with cancer.
example.tran: 脱咖啡因的咖啡仍含一些刺激物和其他可能致癌的有害物质。

value.tran: 令人不快的人(或事);危害别人的人(或事)
